	<Title>
		Recipe: Seasonal fruit palette
	</Title>
	<Abstract />
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Made to look like a painter&apos;s palette, this dessert is festive looking with the star fruit. If you prefer, you can replace any of the fruits with other options, including apples, nectarines, grapes or apricots.&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;In a small bowl, stir together the cinnamon and sugar. Set aside.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In a food processor or blender, combine the strawberries and powdered sugar. Pulse until smooth. Pour onto chilled dessert plates that have a rim. Arrange the sliced fruit on top. Sprinkle with the cinnamon-sugar mixture. Garnish with fresh mint and serve immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;p&gt;1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon&lt;br /&gt;
1/4 teaspoon sugar&lt;br /&gt;
2 cups frozen strawberries, unsweetened (thawed)&lt;br /&gt;
1/2 cup powdered sugar&lt;br /&gt;
1 star fruit, sliced&lt;br /&gt;
1 peach, pitted and sliced&lt;br /&gt;
1 pear, pitted and sliced&lt;br /&gt;
1 plum, pitted and sliced&lt;br /&gt;
1 kiwi, peeled and sliced&lt;br /&gt;
Fresh mint leaves, for garnish&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Ingredients>
